{ This will get crazy, but Black will have a nice advantage - at least! } 6...
Qg5 7. Nxc6 Qxg2 8. Rf1 a6 9. Nxd5
{ After this move, White will have a hard time not losing quickly. Here  9.Ba4  Nxc3  10.dxc3  Qe4+  11.Qe2  Qxe2+  12.Kxe2  Bd7  is White's relatively best option, but Black is still slightly better. }
9... axb5 10. Nxc7+ Kd7 11. Nxa8 Kxc6
{ Black's King has taken a rather unusual post, but general considerations are irrelevant here. We need to check everything move-by-move - and White ends up in miserable shape. For the Quickstarter, I suggest stopping at this point. The line is rare, and it's OK to check the fascinating complications at a later stage by studyingthe full chapter. }
