{ We'll examine this move in the Quickstarter. It is the most popular, but White has tried various alternatives. Inthe full chapter, we'll take a closer look at these options. }
14... Rfd8
{ I suggest moving to d8 in reply to Bh6, also in other cases. So unless you have a strong argument in favor of another move: just go to d8. It makes sense there, opposing the queen and later taking aim at the d4-pawn, which will be a target after c3 has dropped. }
15. Qf3 Qxc3 16. Qf6 Bf8 { And Black has equal chances. } *

