5. Qxd4 Nf6 6. Nc3 Be7 7. Bg5 Nc6 8. Qh4 d6 9. O-O-O Be6
{ This is the key idea to remember. We need to trade this dangerous bishop or we will gain a bit of time if White avoids the trade. Note that Black has not castled and needs to keep all options open and decide according to White's next moves. }
