Nd5
{ It is very important to see here that  13...g5  14.Qa4  b5  is no good due to  15.Bxb5  axb5  16.Qxb5  . The threat of Ne5+ is extremely awkward ! The knight move to d5, however, is just very nice for us, destroying White's pawn structure. }
14. Qg3 Nxc3+ 15. bxc3 Bf6
{ With a clear advantage for Black. The king will have a safe place on b8 and a plan with ...g5 will provide good play against the misplaced queen - not to mention Black is a pawn up ! }
