1. e4 e5 2. d4 exd4
{ Played according to the principle that a central pawn should always be taken if it is possible. Now White actually has quite a wide choice of lines. As it turns out Black is fine against all of them. Indeed, against some we are even able to play for an advantage already. }
3. Nf3
{ White is aiming for a Scotch after  3...Nc6  , but we won't allow that to happen as we have better options. }
3... Bc5
{ I also checked  3...Bb4+  , concluding that it is a viable alternative. However, I liked  3...Bc5  even more, so this is the move I suggest playing. A key point is that the simple capture on d4 is now not in any way a Scotch Game transposition, but actually quite comfortable for Black. }
4. Bc4 d6
{ I like this best. After  4...Nc6  we will without justification transpose into dense theory, while  4....Nf6  5.e5  is murky and not advantageous. }
