3... Nc6 4. Qe3
{ This is the best square for the queen. It makes ...d5 harder to play and covers c5, stopping ...Bc5. }
4... Nf6 5. e5
{ This somewhat naive move is objectively very bad for White, but in order to refute it we need to sacrifice a piece. If you want to learn all of the lines following the piece sacrifice to be 100% sure you get it right you will need to spend a lot of time on a line that might never happen. I'll just show you the most important lines and then I suggest you just go for it if the opportunity arises. The resulting positions are hellish for White to defend, in any case. OK, what is it all about ? Let's see the moves ! }
