{ Unfortunately you rarely get these kind of games. } 12. cxd3 Qxd3+ 13. Qxd3
Nxd3 14. Bxd3 O-O-O { Black has a huge advantage. } 15. a3 Rxd3+ 16. Ke2 Re8+
17. Kxd3 Bf5+ 18. Kc4 Re4+ 19. Kb3 Na5+ 20. Ka2 Be6+ 21. b3 Re2+ 22. Bd2 Bxd2
23. Nbxd2 Nxb3 24. f5 Bd5 25. Kb2 Nxd2 26. Nxd2 Rxd2+ 27. Kc3 Rxg2
{ And after a long a forcing sequence we have reached a clearly better ending for Black. }
