 don't want to allow White to 'get away' with his cheeky opening choice too easily by playing something too 'soft'.   Alright, we should look at some moves now. Just one thing: If your opponent plays the King's Gambit you instantly know he means business. He's ready to hit hard, so we need to be ready to hit back harder. This means your opponent will very likely get the type of game he wanted, but at the same time he will often be just worse! Be mentally ready for this type of game - there won't be any subtle manoeuvring in this game! }
