{ Not losing time with a retreat or covering move. But this move can't be critical. }
6... fxe6 7. Nf3 Qf6
{ Here f6 is an even better square than the usual h6. Black is much better already. We are close to castling queenside and the white king will be in the line of fire even if he regains the pawn - which I don't see happening either. We have ...g5 to cover our booty, and the queen on f6 makes it easier to play this, allowing ...h6 to lend additional cover. }
