{ Black takes care of the pin immediately. Whenever White has played the pawn to e5, the pawn push to g5 gains in strength.   The issue is that at this precise moment  7...g5  is not great due to  8.e6!  ,  intending Ne5. }
8. Bxc6+ bxc6 9. O-O g5
{ Black is materially up and there is no attack in sight for White. Black may go for a setup with Be6, Be7 and Ng7 here. }
