4. Bc4 { White plays in gambit style, not protecting the central pawn. } 4...
Nxe4
{ Of course. If tactically possible, you should take e4 almost all of the time. Centre pawns are important ! }
5. Qe2
{ The only somewhat interesting try. We have ...d5 under even better circumstances against other moves. }
5... d5
{ Instead  5...Qe7  is the greedy move, but  5...d5  leads to a very comfortable game and is easy to play. }
6. Bxd5 Qxd5 7. Nc3 Qe6 8. Nxe4 Nc6
{ Black enjoys the pair of bishops in an open position. Note that ...f5 and/or Nb4 is annoying for White as well. }
