{ This looks odd, but it has a very aggressive idea in mind. White needs to do something concrete anyway, as slow moves just lead to Black being comfortably better. }
5... Be7 6. d4 O-O { Please avoid  6...d6  7.exd6  Qxd6  8.Qb5+  . } 7. g4
{ This is the real idea behind the early queen move. It ultimately fails, but it is useful to know what the best reply is. }
7... fxg3 8. Qg2 d6
{ This is the key idea to remember. Black needs to attack White's centre and prepare ...Bg4. }
9. hxg3 Bg4
{ Black is fine here, with ...Nc6 and ...Qd7 coming next if White just develops. }
10. Nh2 { This gets refuted immediately. } 10... Nxg3 11. Nxg4 Nxh1 12. Qxh1
dxe5 13. Bd3 Bh4+ 14. Kf1 Nc6 { And Black has a winning position. } *

