[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "2. Bishop's Opening, Vienna"]
[Black "Bishop's Opening, Vienna: 1 e4 e5 2.Bc4/Nc3/rare lines #36"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. c3
{ Extremely rare, but I'd like to show a line to illustrate a point. } 2... d5
3. exd5 Qxd5 { The queen is fine on d5 because Nc3 is not available to White. }
4. d4 Nc6 5. Nf3 Nf6
{ The trade on d4 wouldn't be bad, but it is better to delay this exchange to avoid any Nc3. Black has an easy game here. Of course, 2. c3 is very obscure, but it is good to know that ...d5 and Qxd5 is usually fine with a pawn on c3, a motif also well-known from the Alapin Sicilian. }
*

