[White "2. Bishop's Opening, Vienna"]
[Black "Bishop's Opening, Vienna: 1 e4 e5 2.Bc4/Nc3/rare lines #39"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Bb5
{ The Portuguese Opening, a very rare line. Black is fine with many setups, but playing in the same style with which we answer  2.Bc4  makes a lot of sense. }
2... Nf6 3. d3 c6 4. Ba4 Na6
{ This seems to be best, playing against the bishop on a4. Now Black will either get this bishop or White needs to play the c-pawn. }
5. c3 d5
{ Black has reached a favourable version of the mentioned 2. Bc4 Nf6 3. d3 c6 line, and is at least equal. }
