{ @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1@@EndFEN@@ This will most likely transpose to the main line that usually starts with  1.e4  e5  2.Bc4  Nf6  3.d3  c6  4.Nf3  d5  5.Bb3  .  If you like a low maintenance alternative I suggest 4... Be7, setting up with ...d6 later. This is very similar to a Closed Philidor formation where White has played rather timidly with an early d3. This line is better suited to keep it complicated and avoid trades. }
