8. Ne1 Bd6
{ Lokander mentions the sharp  8...f5  , and I agree that it is an interesting move. However, I feel my recommendation is more in line with a Petroff based repertoire. }
9. f3 Bf5
{ Here Caruana has played  9...f5  against Andrew Greet at the Baku Olympiad 2016. Unfortunately, I can't recommend the move as after  10.fxe4  fxe4  11.d4  or  11.Rb1  White is better. }
10. fxe4 Bxe4
{ I think Black should be happy with the result of the opening. His development is good and he has no weaknesses - just what you want in a Petroff based repertoire. }
