5. exd5 Nxd5
{ This is a reversed Scotch Four Knights with White having the extra move h3. This is a useful move, but not enough to offer any advantage for White. }
6. Bb5 Nxc3 7. bxc3 Bd6 8. O-O O-O 9. d4 exd4 10. cxd4 h6
{ This is the main line of the Scotch Four Knights with 10. h3, but with reversed colours and White having h3 extra. A typical way to place Black's pieces is ...Qf6 and ...Bf5. Moving the knight and trying for ...c5 is a standard plan. Note that the pawn structure is actually quite common in the Petroff. }
