ack side after 4. d4 as well, so the position types are familiar. }
4. a3
{ This looks odd, but it involves some ideas. I recommend playing  4...d5  ,  according to the general principle that you should play ...d5 whenever possible. It is still useful to understand that instead  4...Bc5?!  is not great due to  5.Nxe5!  .  We know this idea of course. as 4. Bc4?! Nxe4! is part of our repertoire. But in this version the extra move 5. a3 is very useful, as  5...Nxe5  6.d4  Bd6  7.f4!  shows. Now ...Bb4 would be good, but this is obviously why a3 matters. }
4... d5
{ This is the most principled move and very much according to my approach, to go ...d5 whenever possible. However, I need to mention that the lines are fine for Black, but at times very sharp. This particularly applies to  5.Bb5  Nxe4  6.Nxe5  , where Black is better, but this is very complicated for such a rare line.   If you want to avoid this, I suggest exploring  4...Be7  .  We also examine 4. Be2, which is clearly playable for White - so going for that with the other side having a3 extra can't be terrible. Still, it is best to play  4...d5  and to be ready to challenge White after he has played a move like 4. a3. }
5. Bb5 { This leads to much sharper play, compared to taking on d5. } 5... Nxe4
{ Take this pawn whenever possible - a common theme in this repertoire. Now the best and most popular move is  6.Qe2  , while  6.Nxe5  is downright dubious, but the play gets extremely tactical. }
6. Qe2 Qd6
{ Not the most obvious move, but it is strong. Black protects the centre and the concrete lines work out nicely for us. }
7. Nxe4 dxe4 8. Qxe4 Bd7
{ We have returned the pawn and have prepared to castle queenside quickly. Now we need to check some lines to prove that we are not just losing e5. }
9. d4 O-O-O
{ 9...f5  is also possible if you want to avoid the possible simplifications following queenside castling. }
10. Nxe5 { This is a mistake that can be punished very prettily. } 10... Nxe5
11. dxe5 Qd1+ 12. Kxd1 Bg4+ 13. Ke1 Rd1#
{ Very nice ! I once got this in a blitz game, a sure way to improve your mood. }
*

