6... c5
{ Consistent play, but Black well equipped to deal with the queen sortie. } 7.
Qf4 Nc6 8. Bd3 h6
{ Stockfish already likes Black here. Black has good central pawns, and the coming ...g5! will push the queen around and allow to pressurize the e5 pawn later with ...g4 and/or Bg7. }
9. O-O g5 10. Qf6
{ Not a happy move, but otherwise Black pushes ...g4/...c4 and is just taking over the initiative all over the board. }
10... Qxf6 11. exf6 Bg4
{ Black is better here. We have the more active position and the f-pawn will be an easy target for us. }
