9... O-O 10. Qh5 g6
{ The only move, as  10...h6??  11.Bxh6  is more than unpleasant. } 11. Qh6 Qe7
{ There are other options, but following Kramnik in a Petroff line is a good call almost all of the time. }
12. Bf4 { This was played in V.Gashimov-V.Kramnik, Baku 2009. } 12... f5
{ Kramnik's choice in the game. It leads to interesting play that is about equal. }
13. exf6 Qxf6 14. Bxc7 Qxc3
{ This is no problem at all for Black. Bf5 will be an important resource to trade the dangerous bishop on d3. }
*

