9... dxc4 10. Bxc4 Qxd1 11. Rxd1 Nbd7
{ Black intends to develop with ...Nb6 and then choose the best square for the bishop on c8. Note that the e5-pawn is a possible target if White is not careful. }
12. Nc3 { This looks natural, but it poses no problems at all. } 12... Nb6 13.
Be2 Re8
{ This improves on  13...Bg4  .  The bishop move looks quite normal, but we don't want to trade on f3 and ...Re8 and ...Bf8 makes a lot of sense, taking aim at the e5-pawn. }
14. Nd2 { White is ready to play f4 if necessary, but it looks unimpressive. }
14... Bf5
{ Given the choice, I'd rather be Black here. The engine is on 0.00, as usual. }
*

