{ A direct approach that @@StartBracket@@almost@@EndBracket@@ forces the knight back to e6. The @@StartBracket@@'almost'@@EndBracket@@ is because of the playable  12...b5  , but I suggest to just move the attacked piece. }
12... Ne6 13. a3 Nb6 14. Ba2 Nc7 15. Nc3 Be6
{ And Black had equalized in the game S.Movsesian- D.Fridman, German Bundesliga 2013. GM Daniel Fridman is a Petroff expert and his games are always worth studying. We have been club and team mates for some some years for the team of Muelheim-Nord. During that time he played the Petroff a lot against top level opposition, with good results. }
