1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. d4 Nxe4 4. Bd3 d5 5. Nxe5 Nd7 6. Nxd7 Bxd7 7. Nc3
{ @@StartFEN@@r2qkb1r/pppb1ppp/8/3p4/3Pn3/3B4/PPP2PPP/RNBQK2R w KQkq - 0 7@@EndFEN@@ This does not have significant independent value. It will most often transpose to  7.O-O  Bd6  8.Nc3  . We need to check one deviation though. }
7... Nxc3 8. bxc3 Bd6 9. Qh5
{ @@StartFEN@@r2qkb1r/pppb1ppp/8/3p4/3Pn3/3B4/PPP2PPP/RNBQK2R w KQkq - 0 7@@EndFEN@@ Here 9. O-O transposes to  7.O-O  Bd6  8.Nc3  Nxc3  9.bxc3  . The queen sortie avoids this transposition, but it is not very threatening. }
9... Qe7+ 10. Be3 Bc6
{ Just covering the pawn and castling next after a preparatory ... g6. } 11.
O-O g6 12. Qh3 Qd7
{ And Black has no problems at all - it is about equal. We have the better pawn structure to play for. }
