1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. d4 Nxe4 4. Bd3 d5 5. Nxe5 Nd7 6. Nxd7 Bxd7 7. Nd2
{ Not very ambitious, but certainly very solid. } 7... Nxd2
{ This is enough to prove that 7. Nd2 is lame, but if you want to have more fun, you may also play  7...f5  .  There is not much to analyze here, simply play ...Qf6 and then O-O-O. }
