12... dxc4 13. Qxc4 Nd7
{ A common structure that is generally fine for Black unless White has some concrete dangerous possibility @@StartBracket@@for example attacks on f7 or h7@@EndBracket@@. Here White has nothing special, so Black is fine. }
14. Qb3 Qc7
{ Most of the time this is a good post for the queen in such a pawn structure. We cover b7 and connect the rooks. }
15. c4 Rfe8 16. Bb2 Nf6
{ And again I think it is about equal. White's pawns look pretty in the centre, but they don't advance quickly and trades on the e-file will take away any possible attacking potential that White may have. }
