{ Anand decided to close the queenside, avoiding the tactical lines that would open up the centre quickly. }
14... Bxe5 15. dxe5 Ng5 16. Bb2
{ White's idea is to play Nd2 and f4, harrassing the knight on g5. } 16... Bxd3
{ This is the improvement on Caruana's  16...d4  , which did not work out well for him. After the better move Black is completely fine according to Vishy Anand's annotations in NIC magazine. }
17. Qxd3 a5
{ This detail is very important as it allows a later trade on a1. Anand mentions the alternative  17...g6  18.f4  Ne4  19.Nd2  Nxd2  20.Qxd2  Ne6  21.Rae1  and White keeps more attacking potential on the board. }
18. f4 Ne4 19. Nd2 axb4 20. axb4 Rxa1 21. Bxa1 Nxd2 22. Qxd2 Qh4
{ Black is perfectly fine here. After the trades White's ideas on the kingside are not dangerous anymore. }
