15... Bg5
{ The engine also likes  15...d5  here, but the line I am suggesting seems very logical to me. }
16. f4 Bf6 17. Bxf6 gxf6
{ Here both sides have pawn structure issues, making it about equal. White only has one direct attempt to shake Black's defence. }
18. f5 Bxf5 19. Qxh6 Bg4
{ And the idea to trade h5 for f6 by going ...Rh8 or ...Rg5 will equalize the game. }
