13... a6
{ Caruana played  13...c5  here. I prefer to not play this move at all in these structures. My main issue with this pawn structure is that on top of the d5-square and d6-pawn we also somewhat weaken the king safety. However, we need to mention that although White eventually won Black was still OK initially. After  13...c5  14.Be3  O-O-O  , improving on Caruana's  14...d5  , annotator Anish Giri concludes that White has nothing special. He's got slight pressure, but no substantial advantage.  I am recommending 13... a6 here, which just transposes to the line starting with 11. Be2 a6 12. Nd4 Nxd4 13. Bxd4 Rg8. }
