11. a3 a6
{ This would be a really funny sequence of moves. From the tabiya on move 10 both sides just play their flank pawns one square and then reconsider. This particular position I don't find in my database, but the possible play from here is fairly typical. }
12. Nd4 Nxd4 13. Bxd4 Rg8 14. c4 O-O-O
{ And we reach a common middlegame type for the modern main line. } *

