14. Be2 Qa4 15. b3 Qa5 16. f4 Bxd4 17. Qxd4 Rhg8
{ Here Caruana went for  17...g6  against MVL. He held quite comfortably, but I suggest to not weaken f6 for the moment. In the mentioned game  17...g6  18.h5  Qc5  was played and now  19.Qf6  would have been more testing than the game move  19.Qd2  . With the rook move we prevent this possibility. }
18. g4 Qc5 19. Qd2 Rge8
{ Black is OK in this position. White has more space, but there is little to attack in black's solid setup. White has gained space, but ...Bd7-c6 is an interesting idea to improve. We also have weak spots on the e-file like e3 that we may use. }
