{ We always castle short in this chapter. There is nothing wrong about going for ...O-O-O, either. You could argue that the bishop on f4 is not ideally placed to fight ...O-O-O, as it exerts no pressure on a7. The choice between queenside and kingside castling is a matter of taste. In this chapter, we'll focus on ...O-O, which is somewhat more confrontational. }
