11... Be6 12. Qf4 { Intead  12.Rhe1  would transpose to 11. Rhe1 Be6 12. Bg5. }
12... h6
{ This is the cleanest way to prove that Black is fine. White's sacrifice on h6 only leads to a draw now. The alternative  12...d5  is possible, too. }
13. Bxh6 gxh6 14. Qxh6 Re8
{ Clearing the way for ...Bf8. Now  15.Qg5+  Kf8  16.Qh6+  is the simple draw, so we need to check the more interesting alternative 15. Ng5. }
15. Ng5 Bf8 16. Bh7+ Kh8 17. Qh4 Ng4
{ A key move! We threaten ...Qxg5+! now, followed by ...Bh6. The following line is extremely long, but completely forced. }
18. Bf5+ Bh6 19. f4 Qf6 20. Bxe6 Qxf4+ 21. Kb1 fxe6 22. Nh3 Qf5 23. Rdf1 Qg6
24. Rf4 Ne3 25. Rf6 Qxc2+ 26. Ka1 Nf5 27. Qh5 Re7 28. Ng5 Qxg2 29. Rxh6+ Nxh6
30. Qxh6+ Kg8 31. Qg6+ Rg7
{ And White needs to force the draw now after  32.Qxe6+  Kh8  33.Qh6+  Kg8  34.Qe6+  . }
