17. Rdxd5
{ The best move. After  17.Rf5?  Qxf4+  18.Rxf4  Bd8  19.Bd3  g5  Black is much better because White's forces are uncoordinated. }
17... Re7
{ A very important point! We can't play  17...Bxe5?  18.Nxe5  Rec8  due to  19.Rd7!  , which is crushing.   After the best move,  17...Re7!  , White's rooks are attacked for real. White has some options now, but Black is fine in all lines. Here's one that is worth knowing. }
18. Rxc5 Bxe5 19. Rxe5 Bxa2 20. Nh4 Rxe5 21. Ng6+ Ke8 22. Nxe5 Be6
{ With about equal chances. White's pawns are not dangerous yet, which is important in this type of material distribution. }
