12... c4
{ Dhopade suggests this move and labels it as a novelty. Some months later, in 2021, the move has been tested already on the highest level, in an online blitz game between Fabiano Caruana @@StartBracket@@white!@@EndBracket@@ and Jan-Krysztof Duda. Black wants to push away the d3-bishop and gain access to the e4-square for the knight. This sounds attractive, but it has a drawback in giving up control of the d4-square. These abstract considerations have to be supported by concrete analysis, of course. }
13. Bf1
{ 13.Be2  is quite similar and should transpose to our line after  13...Ne4  14.Qd4  d5  15.Bxc4  . }
13... Ne4 14. Qe2
{ Caruana's choice in the mentioned blitz game against Duda. White is in some trouble now, as the Black attack is gaining momentum quickly. }
14... d5
{ Black has two main attacking ideas: playing ...Qa5, threatening to sacrifice on a3 or c3, and the pawn storm featuring ...b5 and ...a5. }
15. Bd4
{ Caruana covers the c3-square, which helps to defend against the ...Qa5-plan. Against  15.Nd4  this plan would work well:  15...Qa5  16.Nxe6  Bxa3!  17.Rxd5  Bxb2+  18.Kxb2  Qxc3+  19.Ka2  fxe6  20.Rh5  Qb4  21.Bd4  c3  22.Qb5  Qxd4  is an instructive line to illustrate this attacking scheme.. }
15... b5
{ Black had a large advantage in F.Caruana - J.Duda, online Blitz 2020. Black's attack on the queenside is dangerous and easy to play. }
